{{Quote|For the hunters, it was a very good day.|[[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]]|<ref name="XWRS25" />}}
The '''Battle of Derra IV''' was an engagement between the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] convoy near the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Derra IV/Legends|Derra IV]].

==Build up==
[[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]], while [[Capture of Zekka Thyne|working]] to undermine the influence of the criminal organization known as [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]], discovered that the weapon-smuggling freighter ''[[Hopskip]]'' was bound for Derra IV. This information, combined with other evidence gathered by [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]], demonstrated that a Rebel supply convoy was intending to depart from that planet to the new Rebel base. [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and Thrawn worked together to develop the plan that would send the [[181st Imperial Fighter Wing/Legends|181st Imperial Fighter Group]] to eliminate them.

Vader presented this plan to the pilots, though one of them [[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]] recognized that the plan was the brainchild of the quiet alien Admiral. This act left Fel irritated, disgusted at the hypocrisy of an alien being relied upon as the savior of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]], when [[High Human Culture/Legends|Human superiority]] was a major premise used to justify Imperial policies. Ironically, Thrawn would receive no credit for his role in the battle, and Fel would later serve under Thrawn's fellow [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] in the [[Empire of the Hand]].

==Battle==
{{Quote|A huge force of TIE fighters jumped Commander Narra and the convoy off Derra IV. Cut them to pieces. There were no survivors.|General [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Carlist Rieekan]]|<ref name="ESBr" />}}
The convoy soon left Derra IV, but before it could enter [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], a [[Imperial II-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] appeared, and the TIE fighters of the 181st pounced on the unsuspecting Rebel ships. Despite the best efforts of [[Renegade Flight]] to defend the convoy, it was utterly destroyed. Soon afterward, Renegade Flight, which was part of [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Red Squadron]], met its end as well, with [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Arhul Narra/Legends|Narra]] dying at the hands of Fel himself.

==Aftermath==
The battle, although relatively insignificant and rather one sided, was a major victory for the Empire. The three major players in the 181st ([[Turr Phennir]], [[Evir Derricote]] and Soontir Fel) were promoted in a major ceremony on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] presided over by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] himself. Phennir was given command of the 181st's second squadron and promoted to Commander for destroying four Rebel transports; Derricote was placed in charge of the Imperial facility on [[Borleias/Legends|Borleias]] and promoted to [[General/Legends|General]]; and Fel was promoted to [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]], given command of the 181st, and granted the [[Fel estate]] on his native [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] as a [[Baron of the Empire/Legends|Baron of the Empire]], to which he moved his family shortly thereafter.

Though the plan was put together by Thrawn, he received no credit for the battle. As he was already a Grand Admiral at the time, there was perhaps no further honor he could receive. Some suggested that [[Ysanne Isard]] had the Emperor afterwards reassign Thrawn to the Unknown Regions to avoid the embarrassment of an alien's strategic achievement.

Moreover, the battle left the Rebel defenses at [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] badly understaffed, with no opportunity for resupply and with only the forces of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Flight]] to defend them. Following the death of Commander Narra, [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] of Rogue Flight was promoted to Commander and took control of Red Squadron, which he soon after molded into [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]].

This battle would later be made into a simulation for [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] pilots to attempt. While kept in captivity on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] in [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] tried this simulation with no luck.

